<!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-size:xx-small;">Personal photo image of Elric by Joseph Michael Linsner</span><!--EZCODE FONT END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=khurai>Khurai</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/17/03 7:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2214.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://mydata.salve.edu/paduaj/khutze.gif width=136 height=182></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Neon Genesis Evangelion</span><hr size=1> That's honestly something I never really thought about. The angels, while obviously intelligent in battle and other ways (ie &quot;hacking&quot; into the nerv computer system), had this air of just a killing machine. It always seemed convienient that the angels would attack near nerv so the Evas could save the day. <br>
<br>
But now that I think of it... they were always after the angel that Nerv had in the basement. Memory might be failing here, but was that Adam? The first angel that appeared in the Antarctica when Misato was a child? I remember it being mentioned that if an angel were to come in contact with Adam that the second comming would occur. (or apocalypse, or whatever term they used). Maybe that would explain why they were always attacking Nerv.<br>
<br>
But then there is Ikari's involvement. You were never quite sure if he was just rolling with the punches or if somehow he had orchestrated <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>everything</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->. And if so, then was it really the angels agenda, or did Ikari just use them as well to meet his own needs?<br>
<br>
Hate to answer a question with a question, its just been awhile since Ive seen the show so its all speculation. I plan on pulling them out this weekend, so maybe I'll have more to add then. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  My biggest curiosity is still Ikari and Rei. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gothmatum>Gothmatum</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Necro Extraordinare<br>
CN's Major-Domo<br>
I Need Serenity</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/18/03 1:36 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2214.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://users.zoominternet.net/~gothmatum/images/lilgoth.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Neon Genesis Evangelion</span><hr size=1> To answer your questions...<br>
<br>
The Angel in Terminal Dogma was Lilith, the Second Angel.  Adam was reduced to embryotic form in the Second Impact (the simultaneous detonation of several N2 mines).  He was kept in deep freeze until Ikari basically called for him (courtesy of Kaji).  <br>
<br>
Speaking of Gendo Ikari... his agenda all along was to reunite with his wife, Yui.  The best way to do that for certain was to initiate Third Impact in a way he could control, and free the soul of his wife from Eva-01 as his own is freed from his body.  <br>
<br>
The Dead Sea Scrolls foretold the coming of 17 Angels and that the destruction of the last would be the advent of Armageddon (the Third Impact).  So perhaps NERV was constructed as bait to draw out the Angels so they could be destroyed?<br>
<br>
Or, is it possible the Angels knew what Gendo and/or SEELE were up to and began to assault NERV HQ in an effort to prevent the end of the world?  That would cast the purpose of NERV and the battles of the Evas in an entirely different light...<br>
<br>
Thoughts?<br>
