<br>
As for Shinji choking Asuka, yes the first time is simply in Shinji's head.  He's lashing out at what he sees as a lack of acknowledgement from someone he's come to care deeply about, maybe even love.  While Asuka isn't always such a cold and cruel bitch, Shinji tends to see her that way, because of how &quot;ambiguous&quot; she and all the other females in his life keep things.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Shinji: <br>
But ambiguity only makes me insecure. <br>
(Lit: &quot;pushes me into a corner&quot<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
His mother died (or disappeared), leaving him with his father, who utterly rejects him.  His superior (Misato) is hard on him, Rei ignores him half the time, and Asuka seems to enjoy making him feel about an inch tall.  Everywhere Shinji turns, he's facing more pain and heartache.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Shinji: <br>
Nobody wants me. So, everybody just die. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
If he'd stuck with that sentiment, he'd have given in to Complementation and the human race would have ended.  But he realises that he can't run away (something he faced in the very first episode) and that allowing Complementation when he has the power to stop it is running away from reality.  A world without AT Feilds isn't a 'real' world, a world with individuals, interaction (both good and bad), and the manifestation of hopes, fears, and reams.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Kaworu: <br>
Is it okay for AT Fields to hurt you and others once more? <br>
<br>
Shinji: <br>
I don't mind. But, what are you two within my heart? <br>
<br>
Rei: <br>
Hope. <br>
The hope that people might be able to understand one another. <br>
<br>
Kaworu: <br>
And the words 'I love you'. <br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
(all these quotes are from EoE btw)<br>
<br>
But yes.  Rei had Lilith's genetic code but was fashioned by Gendou to look like Yui.  Again, using her like a doll.<br>
